Cells

Want to show a grid of cells on a screen?

Sure. I'll show you how to do it in loads of different ways.


In each case, we'll make a grid that's 100 wide and 100 high.

Colour cells by changing their background-color style.

const cells = document.querySelectorAll("td");
for (const cell of cells) {
  cell.style.backgroundColor = Math.random() > 0.5 ? "black" : "white";
}


That's it! To celebrate, click anywhere in the grid below to place down a non-mutating huegene.





Addendum

Sigh

Multiple people have complained to me that this approach is not fast enough(!) because of the (intentional) slowness of the above huegene example, which was only ever intended to be a You know what, nevermind. It's okay. I'm fine. I'm not bitter.

But I will prove to you that the table approach is fast enough.


Style

When you're drawing things with just HTML and CSS, you have a lot of tools at your disposal.

For example, you can create a big list of styles that automatically colours your cells based on their contents.


Let's make pink sand. Cells can only be one of two ways: Empty (Black) or Sand (Pink). Store this wherever you want on the cell. Invent an imaginary attribute for it, I don't care. 

<td data-element="sand"></td>

Write some CSS that styles cells based on this attribute.

td[data-element="sand"] {
  background-color: hotpink;
}

td[data-element="empty"] {
  background-color: black;
}

Now you can set the colour of your cells by changing the made up attribute! Here it is.


hey screw it. i'll even add an option that changes the speed of all the simulations on this page. you may have noticed it floating on your screen somewhere. maybe the bottom?

the effects of going "too fast" will differ in the different simulations. but we'll get to that in a later blog post.


i know what some of u are gonna say. ur gonna say "oh but lu its easy when theres only two elements like Empty (Black) and Sand (Pink). but what about when theres lots of colours? ha!"

and that is exactly what splash is for. it lets you set styles in exactly the same way. watch this.
